maybe i am just very tired and very mentally ill tonight. maybe i should go to bed.
i just get confused i guess. do people not usually see online communication as similar to irl communication?

digital responses i do give a pretty big grace period for - if i haven't seen you on the specific application i message you on, then i assume you can't message back yet. but if i do then i'm ??
it's like if you don't pick up my phonecall but then call someone else in front of me

if i don't reply (unless for some reason i've completely blanked) it's usually because i'm upset. i treat digital communication like irl communication. i'm not going to ignore you irl unless i'm upset (or dealing w some massive brainfog). ig other people don't see it that way??

i think a lot of the struggle lies in me just not understanding why people don't reply... like i, even if i don't know what to say or don't have the energy or whatever, will always reply asap. even if it's just with an emoji or something. otherwise it feels weird.
i know that i just have some friends who are absolute shit at replying. i know this. but i still can't help but think they hate me if they don't reply. 🫠

love how in my own head i get about messaging people. /s
if someone doesn't message me back i immediately jump to "ok so they hate me" and i hate that about myself ngl because it makes it hard to feel confident in my friendships
